Package imagingbook.pub.corners

Class MopsCornerDetector

  • java.lang.Object
    • imagingbook.pub.corners.GradientCornerDetector
      • imagingbook.pub.corners.MopsCornerDetector
  • public class MopsCornerDetector
extends GradientCornerDetector
    This is an implementation of the corner detector described in
    M. Brown, R. Szeliski, and S. Winder, Multi-image matching using multi-scale oriented patches, in Proc. of the IEEE Computer Society Conference on Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (CVPR'05), 2005, pp. 510â€“517.
    This class extends GradientCornerDetector (where most of the work is done) by defining a specific corner score function and associated threshold. The corner score is defined as the harmonic mean of the local structure tensor's eigenvalues lambda_1, lambda_2.
    Version:
    2020/10/05
